### **Combining bullet chart and sparklines**

Similarly, we can combining the bullet chart and sparklines using the steps below.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true" code-summary="Show the code"}
bullet <- coffeechain %>%
  filter(Date >= "2013-01-01") %>%
  group_by(`Product`) %>%
  summarise(`Target` = sum(`Budget Sales`),
            `Actual` = sum(`Sales`)) %>%
  ungroup() 
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true" code-summary="Show the code"}
sales_data = sales_data %>%
  left_join(bullet, by = "Product")
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
names(sales_data)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "Product"       "Min"           "Max"           "Average"      
[5] "Monthly Sales" "Target"        "Actual"       
```


:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true" code-summary="Show the code"}
library(dplyr)
library(gt)
library(gtExtras)

sales_data %>%
  gt() %>%
  gt_plt_sparkline('Monthly Sales') %>%
  gt_plt_bullet(
    column = Actual,
    target = Target,
    width = 28,
    palette = c("lightblue", "black")
  ) %>%
  gt_theme_538()
```

